Hello,
The control crashes (NullReferenceException )when I click on empty space in the control area. The crash is coming from  OnMouseDown(MouseButtonEventArgs e) in SelectionMultiple class (the item is null and the first condition does not check for null when accessing ContextMenu property):

            TreeViewExItem item = GetTreeViewItemUnderMouse(e.GetPosition(treeViewEx));
            if (e.ChangedButton != MouseButton.Left && !(e.ChangedButton == MouseButton.Right && item.ContextMenu != null)) return;

            if (item == null || item.IsEditing) return;

            SelectSingleItem(item);

            FocusHelper.Focus(item);
        }

Just an easy fix - I think worth adding to the official version of the control.

Regards,
Ola
